WEBVTT

00:03.580 --> 00:05.620
[ Water running ]

00:11.330 --> 00:13.500
April:
In the course of one day,

00:13.500 --> 00:16.920
Job received four messages,
each with separate news

00:16.920 --> 00:21.460
that his livestock, servants,
and 10 children had all died.

00:24.920 --> 00:26.540
[ Monitor beeping ]

00:26.540 --> 00:28.580
He continued to be
a faithful servant.

00:28.580 --> 00:31.170
He still praised God.
He persevered.

00:33.170 --> 00:34.670
-What did you do?
-We didn't do this.

00:34.670 --> 00:36.500
My card was in his pocket,
so they called me.

00:36.500 --> 00:38.210
But we were at home.
We were in bed.

00:38.210 --> 00:39.330
April:
Can I get a hand in here?!

00:39.330 --> 00:40.330
Go to the attendant's
lounge on three.

00:40.330 --> 00:41.670
And don't talk
to anybody.

00:41.670 --> 00:44.170
Job's faith was tested.
[ Groans loudly ]

00:44.170 --> 00:45.790
And he passed the test.
[ Groans ]

00:45.790 --> 00:47.880
[ Grunting ]

00:47.880 --> 00:49.620
April:
We've got you. Okay.

00:49.620 --> 00:51.000
Paul: Ahh!
Meredith: Hit-and-run?

00:51.000 --> 00:53.080
Yes. He's just
waking up now.

00:53.080 --> 00:55.790
Dr. Stadler, calm down.
We're trying to help you, okay?

00:55.790 --> 00:57.790
-Feel a little stick here.
-[ Screams ]

00:57.790 --> 01:00.500
-Are there any suspects?
-Why would I know that?

01:00.500 --> 01:02.250
-Okay. You can't lose him.
-I don't intend to.

01:02.250 --> 01:04.540
I mean, you really
can't lose him.

01:04.540 --> 01:06.080
I won't.

01:06.080 --> 01:07.500
Oh. Thanks for the help.

01:07.500 --> 01:08.750
And the vote
of confidence!

01:08.750 --> 01:10.500
And for his faith,

01:10.500 --> 01:13.170
God rewarded Job with
twice what he had before.

01:13.170 --> 01:16.210
Hey, Helm! Get in here
and staple up this head lac

01:16.210 --> 01:18.330
and then get him
up to CT, okay?

01:18.330 --> 01:19.920
[ Telephone rings ]

01:19.920 --> 01:21.580
Hey. So, what happened
to Stadler?

01:21.580 --> 01:23.330
Hit-and-run.
Sending him to CT.

01:23.330 --> 01:25.000
Hey, uh,
Webber just gave me

01:25.000 --> 01:26.880
the Grey Sloan Medical
Innovation contest.

01:26.880 --> 01:28.750
The whole thing.
Kind of freaking out.

01:28.750 --> 01:30.040
Freaking out because
you don't want it?

01:30.040 --> 01:31.670
No. Why wouldn't I want it?

01:31.670 --> 01:34.330
Uhh, I just think you'd
want to compete is all.

01:34.330 --> 01:36.540
Who wants to compete
when you can be the judge?

01:36.540 --> 01:38.620
Um, everyone?

01:38.620 --> 01:40.670
Ev--

01:40.670 --> 01:43.000
He -- He played me?

01:43.000 --> 01:44.880
Is that what you're saying?
Dr. Webber played me?

01:44.880 --> 01:47.080
I said nothing of the sort.

01:47.080 --> 01:48.250
But yes.
[ Inhales sharply ]

01:48.250 --> 01:51.290
And now I'm gonna go over there.
[ Chuckles ]

01:51.290 --> 01:53.880
He...

01:53.880 --> 01:55.790
Thank you.

01:57.500 --> 01:59.920
Hey, Kepner, I heard
that Dr. Stadler was --

01:59.920 --> 02:02.210
He's gone to CT. He should
be fine. And you know what?
That's good.

02:02.210 --> 02:04.330
Um, I've been
reconsidering it,

02:04.330 --> 02:07.000
and -- and I think
that you're fully capable

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
of running that contest
on your own.

02:09.000 --> 02:10.670
I mean, I-I think --

02:10.670 --> 02:12.620
I think that your "seasons"
make you the exact right man --

02:12.620 --> 02:14.330
No.

02:14.330 --> 02:16.710
No? You didn't even --
You didn't even think about it.

02:16.710 --> 02:19.080
Finders keepers,
Kepner.

02:19.080 --> 02:20.500
That's very childish,
Dr. Webber!

02:20.500 --> 02:21.960
Richard:
Finders keepers!

02:21.960 --> 02:23.330
Karin Taylor.
30 years old.

02:23.330 --> 02:25.080
37 weeks pregnant
with active contract--

02:25.080 --> 02:27.420
Nope! Very pregnant
patients go to L&D.

02:27.420 --> 02:28.670
I'm not due for
another three weeks.

02:28.670 --> 02:30.920
I can't reach my husband, so I'm
hoping that this is false labor,

02:30.920 --> 02:32.460
but Dr. Robbins said
that she would meet me here.

02:32.460 --> 02:34.620
-Dr. Robbins? Okay.
-[ Exhales sharply ] Mm-hmm.

02:34.620 --> 02:36.170
She's my maternal-fetal doc.

02:36.170 --> 02:37.830
My baby's got a --
a teeny heart defect.

02:37.830 --> 02:39.710
Ohh! Ahh!
Here comes another one.

02:39.710 --> 02:41.620
Hmm! Motherhumper!
This hurts!

02:41.620 --> 02:43.880
April: Ah.
[ Laughing ] Ah. Okay.

02:43.880 --> 02:46.080
-[ Exhales sharply ]
-All right. Here you go.

02:46.080 --> 02:48.460
Just breathe.

02:48.460 --> 02:50.500
[ Breathing heavily ]
I don't like to question God,

02:50.500 --> 02:52.880
but I have got to wonder
about this particular design.

02:52.880 --> 02:55.540
I mean, the combination of
the size of the baby's head

02:55.540 --> 02:58.000
and the female anatomy,
it just feels like...
One, two, three!

02:58.000 --> 03:00.880
...an odd act of cruelty,
or, like, maybe a
little bit of a slip.

03:00.880 --> 03:03.080
Like, maybe he was tipsy
when he came up with it.

03:03.080 --> 03:05.500
I mean, we know God
likes to drink -- the whole
"water to wine" of it all.

03:05.500 --> 03:07.960
It just doesn't seem like that
far of a leap to think that --

03:07.960 --> 03:09.380
Ohh! Ooh!

03:09.380 --> 03:11.920
Son of a fish!
This hurts!
Okay.

03:11.920 --> 03:14.040
These contractions are
pretty close together.

03:14.040 --> 03:15.580
Do you mind if I do
a quick exam?

03:15.580 --> 03:17.540
-[ Exhales sharply ]
-No? Okay. Here we go.

03:20.210 --> 03:21.830
Uh-oh. What's wrong?
What's that face?

03:21.830 --> 03:24.040
Uh, n-no, nothing's wrong.
It's just this baby's

03:24.040 --> 03:26.380
not waiting for anyone,
'cause I can feel the head.

03:26.380 --> 03:28.210
No, no, no. My husband is gonna
die if he doesn't make it here.

03:28.210 --> 03:31.170
Because I am
going to kill him!

03:31.170 --> 03:33.330
Answer the phone!
We've got
a precipitous delivery.

03:33.330 --> 03:35.540
Helm, get an L&D tray
and a baby warmer.

03:35.540 --> 03:37.120
And somebody
find me Robbins!

03:37.120 --> 03:39.460
Ben: [ Sighs ]
Miranda, I'm sorry.

03:39.460 --> 03:41.500
But it's a teacher
work day and --

03:41.500 --> 03:43.380
Which is why I signed him up
for Science Camp.

03:43.380 --> 03:45.170
No, actually,
you asked me to do it,

03:45.170 --> 03:47.380
and I forgot,
and I'm sorry.

03:47.380 --> 03:49.620
But they changed my
ride-along to today.

03:49.620 --> 03:53.920
Oh, so your plan now is to
leave me with two tween-age boys

03:53.920 --> 03:55.880
while you go ride around
with your friends all day

03:55.880 --> 03:57.460
in the ambulance.

03:57.460 --> 03:59.580
Well, I'm not joyriding,
Miranda. I'm gonna go on --

03:59.580 --> 04:02.380
Okay, we're not arguing
right now about your
questionable career choices.

04:02.380 --> 04:06.420
We are arguing about your
failure to secure childcare.

04:06.420 --> 04:09.540
[ Sighs ] Yeah, fine. Go.
I'll think of something.

04:09.540 --> 04:11.380
Mnh.

04:11.380 --> 04:13.380
[ Rattling ]
Hmph.

04:14.750 --> 04:16.710
Hey! Tuck is here!

04:16.710 --> 04:19.670
Yes. He's supposed to be at
Science Camp, but my husband --

04:19.670 --> 04:22.330
[ Gasps ] Ooh, Science Camp.
I loved Science Camp.

04:22.330 --> 04:24.880
Ohh! They can't miss that.
That's cruel.

04:24.880 --> 04:27.120
-Let me do it!
-Hmm?

04:27.120 --> 04:29.380
Can I do a science camp?
Can I take them?

04:29.380 --> 04:31.500
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
I'm canceling a thing.
I'll be right back!

04:35.120 --> 04:36.170
Okay.

04:36.170 --> 04:37.790
[ Karin screaming ]

04:37.790 --> 04:40.420
Okay, Karin, just relax.
You're doing great.

04:40.420 --> 04:42.000
Karin: I feel like I'm
pooping out a cantaloupe.

04:42.000 --> 04:43.250
Okay.
We can help with that.

04:43.250 --> 04:44.330
-Um, Dr. Helm.
-Mm-hmm?

04:44.330 --> 04:45.750
See this area right here,
the perineum?

04:45.750 --> 04:47.380
I want you to place
your hand right here

04:47.380 --> 04:49.000
and, with your thumb
and index, form a "U."

04:49.000 --> 04:51.210
That'll help relieve
some of the pressure
and keep her from tearing.

04:51.210 --> 04:52.380
-Tearing?
-Tearing?!

04:52.380 --> 04:53.540
-We're preventing that.
-Ooh!

04:53.540 --> 04:55.380
It's just I -- Ooh.

04:55.380 --> 04:56.540
I always, uh -- Hmm.
[ Karin screaming ]

04:56.540 --> 04:59.210
I can never get over how
it just stretches like that.

04:59.210 --> 05:00.710
This whole process defies
the laws of physics.

05:00.710 --> 05:02.080
I mean,
it's almost inhuman.

05:02.080 --> 05:04.080
"Miraculous."
She means miraculous, Karin.

05:04.080 --> 05:05.620
My whole hand
fits in here!

05:05.620 --> 05:07.500
It -- That should never
be able to happen!

05:07.500 --> 05:09.040
Dr. Helm.

05:09.040 --> 05:10.290
[ Karin moaning ]

05:10.290 --> 05:11.750
-Okay, here we go.
-Uh-huh.

05:11.750 --> 05:13.710
-I want you to push. Ready?
-Mm-hmm.

05:13.710 --> 05:16.460
You've got this. Breathe.
Just breathe through this.

05:16.460 --> 05:18.620
If my husband does not
get here in five minutes,

05:18.620 --> 05:20.830
I am gonna personally
shove a cantaloupe up --

05:20.830 --> 05:22.830
-Oh, thank God!
-You all right? How we doing?

05:22.830 --> 05:25.460
How are we doing? You want
to know how we're doing?
You seem fine.

05:25.460 --> 05:27.620
I have got two people's hands
inside me,

05:27.620 --> 05:29.710
one person trying to come out,
and everybody's got an opinion

05:29.710 --> 05:31.620
on my vagina, and you want
to know how we're doing?

05:31.620 --> 05:32.920
April:
She's almost here!

05:34.290 --> 05:36.580
[ Sighs ] April?

05:38.290 --> 05:39.500
Matthew?

05:39.500 --> 05:41.330
April?
This is April?!

05:43.790 --> 05:49.790
AAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHH!

06:03.290 --> 06:05.580
[ Woman on P.A.
speaking indistinctly ]

06:07.460 --> 06:09.120
Meredith: I'm not sure
you guys should be here,

06:09.120 --> 06:10.420
or even in the country.

06:10.420 --> 06:11.920
It wasn't us.

06:11.920 --> 06:13.580
I know. I believe you.

06:13.580 --> 06:15.960
I still think you could make it
to Canada by lunchtime.

06:15.960 --> 06:17.710
Amelia: There's no acute
abnormalities on the CT.

06:17.710 --> 06:19.250
It just looks like
a severe concussion.

06:19.250 --> 06:20.460
He's a lucky guy.

06:20.460 --> 06:22.290
[ Exhales sharply ]
Thanks, Amelia.

06:22.290 --> 06:25.170
So, attempted murder.
Not murder.

06:25.170 --> 06:26.380
We didn't do it.

06:26.380 --> 06:28.250
I know. I believe you.

06:28.250 --> 06:29.540
I'm just not sure
the police will.

06:29.540 --> 06:31.960
Well, there might be some
other possibility here.

06:31.960 --> 06:35.000
Oh, my God.
It was Jenny.

06:35.000 --> 06:36.580
[ Gasps ]

06:36.580 --> 06:38.750
You saw her when she left
with him. She was terrified.

06:38.750 --> 06:41.040
I told her it would
only get worse. She
did this because of me!

06:41.040 --> 06:42.920
Accessory to
attempted murder.

06:42.920 --> 06:45.040
-That's not funny.
-You know what's not funny?

06:45.040 --> 06:46.710
[ Ringtone chimes ]
Canada.

06:46.710 --> 06:48.920
I mean, at the very least, you
two should speak to a lawyer.

06:48.920 --> 06:53.960
♪♪

06:53.960 --> 06:55.880
I have to talk to her.

06:55.880 --> 06:57.580
No. No, no, no.
You can't talk to her.
Why?

06:57.580 --> 07:00.830
No matter who did or didn't
do what. It doesn't matter.

07:00.830 --> 07:03.040
It'll look like
we're conspiring.

07:06.880 --> 07:09.830
[ Monitor beeping ]

07:09.830 --> 07:12.080
You couldn't tell me
you were treating my
jilted fiancé's wife?

07:12.080 --> 07:15.620
I couldn't, 'cause HIPAA.
I wanted to so badly.

07:15.620 --> 07:18.080
-[ Sighs ]
-Dr. Robbins?

07:18.080 --> 07:19.620
Yeah? Oh, hey.
Um, all right.

07:19.620 --> 07:22.250
Well, this one's, uh, got
a NICU bed with her name on it,

07:22.250 --> 07:23.790
so let's take her up
and get her work-up.

07:23.790 --> 07:26.830
Okay, yeah. You know,
that couple is so nice.

07:26.830 --> 07:28.960
T-They remind me
of, uh, of --

07:28.960 --> 07:30.380
That's it --
She reminds me of you.

07:30.380 --> 07:33.750
Heh. Let's go.
[ Baby coos ]

07:33.750 --> 07:35.460
All right. I'm gonna go up with
the baby and get settled.

07:35.460 --> 07:37.420
Mm-hmm.

07:37.420 --> 07:40.250
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Mahoney to the E.R.

07:40.250 --> 07:42.580
Dr. Mahoney to the E.R.

07:42.580 --> 07:44.620
So, Matthew's here.

07:44.620 --> 07:46.080
-Matthew?
-Mm. Mm-hmm.

07:46.080 --> 07:47.460
-Wait. Matthew?
-Yeah.

07:47.460 --> 07:50.580
His wife just had a baby,
emergently, in my arms.

07:50.580 --> 07:52.210
Which was --

07:52.210 --> 07:55.120
Ironic? Comical?
Soul-crushing?

07:55.120 --> 07:56.420
How 'bout we change
the subject?

07:56.420 --> 07:58.040
Mm-hmm.

07:58.040 --> 08:00.380
Hey, you know that
medical innovation contest

08:00.380 --> 08:03.380
Bailey's been talking about?
Anonymous donor, high stakes?

08:03.380 --> 08:05.040
I -- Yeah, I do.

08:05.040 --> 08:06.710
Yeah, I think you should
be in charge of it.

08:06.710 --> 08:09.210
Wh-- Why -- why -- why --
why would that happen?

08:09.210 --> 08:10.420
I mean, hear me out.

08:10.420 --> 08:12.000
You are basically
the head of the board,

08:12.000 --> 08:13.460
you're a brilliant surgeon,
you're an Avery.

08:13.460 --> 08:15.670
This just feels like
something you should do.

08:15.670 --> 08:18.330
And if you want it, which you
should, then you can have it.

08:18.330 --> 08:20.830
Wait, wait. Why is it
yours to give me?

08:20.830 --> 08:22.460
'Cause Webber
gave it to me.

08:22.460 --> 08:24.040
Webber.
Gave it to you?

08:24.040 --> 08:25.960
Woman: Incoming!
[ Siren wailing ]

08:25.960 --> 08:28.540
-Wh--
-Hey, just think about it.

08:28.540 --> 08:29.620
I already did! No!

08:33.460 --> 08:35.420
David Roman, 20.
Attempted suicide.

08:35.420 --> 08:37.540
It wasn't
attempted suicide.

08:37.540 --> 08:39.460
He slashed his wrists
and called 911.

08:39.460 --> 08:41.790
-Uh, call for psych eval.
-I wasn't trying to kill myself.

08:41.790 --> 08:43.830
I-I would never try
to kill myself.

08:43.830 --> 08:45.080
I'd go straight to hell.

08:45.080 --> 08:46.750
-Why'd you cut yourself, then?
-One, two, three.

08:46.750 --> 08:48.540
Matthew 5, verse 30 --

08:48.540 --> 08:52.000
If your right hand causes you
to sin, you cut it off.

08:52.000 --> 08:53.920
And I couldn't stop
sinning.

08:53.920 --> 08:55.080
You mean masturbating?

08:55.080 --> 08:57.080
[ Sighs ]
So I tried to cut it off.

08:57.080 --> 08:58.920
I still think
we need psych.

08:58.920 --> 09:05.620
♪♪

09:05.620 --> 09:07.170
We're just
mixing chemicals!

09:07.170 --> 09:08.790
Can't we, like,
race wheelchairs?

09:08.790 --> 09:11.790
No. So, we have our
hydrogen peroxide.

09:11.790 --> 09:13.960
What we need now
is a catalyst.

09:13.960 --> 09:15.330
[ Liquid pours ]
Who knows what a catalyst is?

09:15.330 --> 09:17.710
-Can we see a dead body?
-No.

09:17.710 --> 09:20.330
A catalyst is a substance
that accelerates another sub--

09:20.330 --> 09:21.830
Okay, I see I'm losing you.

09:21.830 --> 09:24.080
It's a thing that makes
something do something else.

09:24.080 --> 09:27.750
Okay?
So, we pour in our catalyst.

09:27.750 --> 09:30.170
And when they mix...

09:30.170 --> 09:31.290
Step back. Goggles on.

09:35.710 --> 09:38.040
[ Fizzing ]

09:41.880 --> 09:43.750
Blammo!

09:43.750 --> 09:46.290
Wha-- Yes!

09:46.290 --> 09:48.000
That is crazy!

09:48.000 --> 09:49.330
Why does that happen?

09:49.330 --> 09:52.040
Because science!

09:52.040 --> 09:54.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:54.620 --> 09:56.790
Karin,
how are you feeling?

09:56.790 --> 09:58.960
Have you heard anything
about Ruby? About our baby?

09:58.960 --> 10:01.330
They've got her settled
in the NICU, but I haven't
heard an update yet.

10:01.330 --> 10:02.710
You know what? I'll --
I'll go check on her.

10:02.710 --> 10:03.750
Okay.

10:03.750 --> 10:05.920
[ Clears throat ]

10:07.790 --> 10:10.170
If there was something
that was wrong,

10:10.170 --> 10:11.960
Dr. Robbins would have
told you, I'm sure.

10:15.880 --> 10:17.790
Are -- Are you okay?

10:17.790 --> 10:20.120
I'm sorry.
I've just, um...

10:20.120 --> 10:21.960
I've just heard
so much about you.

10:21.960 --> 10:25.040
Right. [ Chuckles ]
Um, that was --

10:25.040 --> 10:26.920
That was a really
complicated time, and --

10:26.920 --> 10:29.000
Oh, gosh. No.
I'm sorry. No.

10:29.000 --> 10:30.790
I don't need to hear
your side of the story.

10:30.790 --> 10:33.120
Truly. Sorry I stared.

10:33.120 --> 10:34.540
It's nice to put
a face to the name.

10:34.540 --> 10:36.540
Right.

10:36.540 --> 10:37.540
So...

10:37.540 --> 10:39.790
Okay.

10:41.620 --> 10:45.330
Chief, what's up?

10:45.330 --> 10:47.670
Ben called.
We got a GSW coming in.

10:47.670 --> 10:48.830
[ Sirens approaching ]

10:48.830 --> 10:50.830
-Are you ready for this?
-Ben called you, too?

10:50.830 --> 10:53.080
-Yeah, he needs an E.N.T.
-Is it bad?

10:53.080 --> 10:54.540
[ Clears throat ]

10:54.540 --> 10:56.620
Wait. Is it --
Is it someone you know?

10:56.620 --> 10:58.500
[ Sirens wailing ]

11:00.580 --> 11:02.080
Eric Sterling.
12 years old.

11:02.080 --> 11:04.170
Vital signs stable.
Airway's intact.

11:04.170 --> 11:07.080
No hard signs
of vascular injury.

11:07.080 --> 11:09.330
Ben: Police shot him in
the neck while he was
climbing through a window,

11:09.330 --> 11:11.330
but Eric says
it was his own house.

11:11.330 --> 11:12.620
[ Ambulance doors close ]

11:12.620 --> 11:15.830
[ Radio chatter ]

11:15.830 --> 11:17.580
So, you gonna take
those cuffs off or what?!

11:17.580 --> 11:18.960
He was breaking into
a house.

11:18.960 --> 11:20.670
He already told you it was
his own damn house!

11:20.670 --> 11:22.000
Look, we weren't
at the scene,

11:22.000 --> 11:23.750
but we were dispatched
to guard the perp.

11:23.750 --> 11:25.500
No, he's not a perp, all right?
If you would just listen to him.

11:25.500 --> 11:27.170
Chad: We have orders,
and we're doing our job.

11:27.170 --> 11:28.250
The suspect's currently
under our --

11:28.250 --> 11:30.420
His name is Eric.

11:30.420 --> 11:33.460
Bailey: Call X-ray for P.A.
and lateral neck films.

11:33.460 --> 11:35.210
Woman: On it!

11:35.210 --> 11:37.880
-Okay. Everybody set?
-Yep.

11:37.880 --> 11:39.960
On my count.
One, two, and three.

11:41.920 --> 11:44.500
We got to get back out there.
Are you with us or with them?

11:46.040 --> 11:48.920
-Ben, we got this.
-Let's go.

11:54.250 --> 11:55.460
All right, Eric,
how you doing?

11:55.460 --> 11:56.620
I want my mom.

11:56.620 --> 11:58.460
I know. I know.
She's on her way.

11:59.620 --> 12:01.290
Officer, I need those cuffs
off him now, not on.

12:01.290 --> 12:02.960
He's still under arrest.
He's unarmed.

12:02.960 --> 12:04.380
He's a 12-year-old kid.
Take 'em off.

12:08.960 --> 12:11.960
Jenny: Sorry.

12:11.960 --> 12:13.790
Woman on P.A.:
Housekeeping, 1-6-1.

12:13.790 --> 12:16.040
Housekeeping, 1-6-1.

12:17.420 --> 12:19.250
Jo.

12:19.250 --> 12:21.380
She really shouldn't
be talking to you.

12:21.380 --> 12:23.460
I know. I just need
one minute, please.

12:23.460 --> 12:25.920
It's okay.

12:28.000 --> 12:29.460
I just want you to know
you don't have to worry.

12:29.460 --> 12:30.710
I didn't tell
the police anything.

12:30.710 --> 12:32.330
What do you mean?

12:32.330 --> 12:34.290
I didn't tell them
it was you.

12:34.290 --> 12:36.830
But thank you.
Thank you so much.

12:45.790 --> 12:49.170
Wait.
I-I was in the hotel.

12:49.170 --> 12:51.170
He got mad and went for a walk
and told me to stay p--

12:51.170 --> 12:53.330
It wasn't you?
I swear to God it wasn't.

12:53.330 --> 12:54.830
Who do you think did it?

12:54.830 --> 12:56.670
An avenging angel?

12:56.670 --> 12:58.080
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:59.710 --> 13:01.380
Sorry.

13:01.380 --> 13:03.620
-No. You don't have to --
-I do.

13:03.620 --> 13:06.170
I really thought
I was better than you.

13:06.170 --> 13:08.420
I believed everything
he told me about you.

13:08.420 --> 13:10.540
God. I'm smart.

13:10.540 --> 13:13.830
I'm a scientist.
I'm a feminist.

13:13.830 --> 13:16.120
I never thought that I would
end up in something like this.

13:16.120 --> 13:18.210
It happened so slow.

13:18.210 --> 13:21.210
I stopped talking
to -- to co-workers,
friends he didn't like.

13:21.210 --> 13:23.080
Then my family didn't
understand. They got worried.

13:23.080 --> 13:24.790
So I just brushed them off

13:24.790 --> 13:26.750
and then stopped
talking to them, too,

13:26.750 --> 13:28.710
and then my circle got smaller
and smaller and smaller

13:28.710 --> 13:30.250
until all I had left
was him.

13:30.250 --> 13:33.170
And then I stopped
believing myself,

13:33.170 --> 13:35.750
things I had seen and heard,
things I knew,

13:35.750 --> 13:38.380
because he told me I was crazy
and I just believed him.

13:38.380 --> 13:39.710
He knows me so well.

13:39.710 --> 13:41.460
He can zero in
on an insecurity

13:41.460 --> 13:43.420
and -- and make a whole
argument turn on a dime,

13:43.420 --> 13:45.080
and now it's my fault --
it's my fault again.

13:45.080 --> 13:46.290
I'm always the one
that's wrong.

13:48.460 --> 13:51.040
When he started hitting me,
it was just barely a surprise.

13:54.120 --> 13:57.880
And he told me it was my fault,
and I actually believed him.

13:57.880 --> 14:00.670
Until you talked
to me yesterday,
I really believed him.

14:00.670 --> 14:02.750
How did I believe him?

14:02.750 --> 14:06.330
Because he was good to you
in the beginning.

14:06.330 --> 14:08.540
And on the good days.

14:08.540 --> 14:10.790
[ Scoffs ]
Jenny, we're not stupid.

14:10.790 --> 14:12.880
We didn't fall for
someone who beat us.

14:12.880 --> 14:15.420
We fell for someone
who made us laugh

14:15.420 --> 14:18.120
and feel wanted
and loved and seen.

14:18.120 --> 14:20.080
Paul is brilliant

14:20.080 --> 14:22.670
and charming
and persuasive,

14:22.670 --> 14:26.080
and the good outweighed the bad
until it didn't.

14:32.120 --> 14:34.330
Okay, uh,
what do we have?

14:34.330 --> 14:36.120
20-year-old tried
to cut off his hand.

14:36.120 --> 14:37.460
He was masturbating
too much.

14:37.460 --> 14:40.710
Oh, my. That seems
like an overreaction.

14:40.710 --> 14:42.040
I was following
God's Word.

14:42.040 --> 14:43.830
Yeah, not quite sure
you heard Him right.

14:43.830 --> 14:45.790
-If you don't know the Bible --
-No, I do. I do.

14:45.790 --> 14:48.000
And the Bible also says
that your body's a temple

14:48.000 --> 14:49.620
and you should use it
to glorify God.

14:49.620 --> 14:52.120
I'm trying to,
but temptation is everywhere.

14:52.120 --> 14:53.540
Yeah, well,
the Bible also says

14:53.540 --> 14:55.250
that God doesn't tempt us
beyond our ability.

14:55.250 --> 14:56.960
He doesn't give us
more than we can handle.

14:56.960 --> 14:58.420
I think handling it
was his problem.

14:58.420 --> 15:00.790
Dr. Roy.
Dr. Roy.

15:00.790 --> 15:03.830
Look. "If your right hand causes
you to sin, you cut it off."

15:03.830 --> 15:06.290
David, when God
created the world, he
also created metaphors.

15:06.290 --> 15:07.830
Excuse me.

15:10.000 --> 15:12.170
[ Radio chatter,
monitor beeping ]

15:16.120 --> 15:17.920
Jackson: I'm not seeing
any sign of bullet fragments,

15:17.920 --> 15:19.620
no vertebral fractures.

15:19.620 --> 15:21.500
I'd like to get
a CT angio.

15:21.500 --> 15:23.920
Yeah, but it's such a high
burden of radiation
for a kid, though.

15:23.920 --> 15:25.960
So our options are
to watch and wait

15:25.960 --> 15:27.460
or to operate blind?

15:27.460 --> 15:28.670
No, thank you.

15:28.670 --> 15:32.000
Let's do the CT.
I'll call up.

15:32.000 --> 15:33.620
We're looking for
Eric Sterling.

15:33.620 --> 15:35.210
Yeah, come this way.

15:39.170 --> 15:41.620
-Mom.
-What happened, baby?

15:41.620 --> 15:44.380
I forgot my key, and they
think I was breaking in.

15:45.790 --> 15:48.620
I would thank you kindly to step
away from my 12-year-old child.

15:48.620 --> 15:50.670
He shouldn't be talking to you
without a guardian present!

15:50.670 --> 15:52.750
He always forgets his keys.
Were you climbing in
the window again?

15:52.750 --> 15:54.710
Yes, but I did go to the
neighbor's house first,

15:54.710 --> 15:56.330
just like you told me to.

15:56.330 --> 15:58.460
-They weren't home.
-And for this you shot him?!

15:58.460 --> 16:00.000
Not us, ma'am.
We weren't at the scene.

16:00.000 --> 16:03.250
I was reaching for my phone
to call you, and they shot me.

16:03.250 --> 16:05.580
How about you direct me to
the one who did the shooting?

16:05.580 --> 16:07.080
Where the hell
is that guy?!

16:07.080 --> 16:09.080
He's at the station
answering some questions.

16:09.080 --> 16:12.000
-Why don't you calm down --
-Calm down? Calm down?!

16:12.000 --> 16:13.500
Calm down.

16:13.500 --> 16:15.830
We'll have a little discussion
about it. Get your I.D. --

16:15.830 --> 16:18.290
You mean after they've had some
time with their kid, right?

16:19.460 --> 16:21.380
He will come speak to you
when he is ready.

16:23.120 --> 16:24.620
Now give him a moment,
please.

16:24.620 --> 16:26.750
[ Radio chatter ]

16:26.750 --> 16:33.120
♪♪

16:33.120 --> 16:35.250
Doctor, I don't tell you
how to do your job.

16:35.250 --> 16:37.000
I'd appreciate you stop
telling me how to do mine.

16:37.000 --> 16:38.580
Are you kidding?

16:38.580 --> 16:40.830
Your co-worker just shot a kid
in the neck for no reason,

16:40.830 --> 16:42.500
and you don't think
that maybe you guys

16:42.500 --> 16:45.500
should figure out another
way to do your job?

16:51.580 --> 16:54.750
[ Breathes deeply ]

16:54.750 --> 16:57.210
[ Clears throat ]

16:57.210 --> 16:59.880
Dr. Kepner, Karin Taylor
is complaining of pain.

16:59.880 --> 17:02.330
[ Telephone rings ]

17:02.330 --> 17:04.790
Karin, you're feeling pain?
Uh, where?

17:04.790 --> 17:06.460
Oh, no.
I'm fine. It's fine.

17:06.460 --> 17:08.790
I was just -- I couldn't find
a comfortable position.

17:08.790 --> 17:11.540
Okay. Your pulse is racing.
I'm just gonna page Dr. Robbins.

17:11.540 --> 17:13.670
Oh, no, please don't.
Ruby's having her heart checked,

17:13.670 --> 17:16.040
and I asked Dr. Robbins and
Matthew to stay with her.

17:16.040 --> 17:17.790
Oh.

17:17.790 --> 17:19.670
Okay, Karin, if you don't
tell me what's going on,

17:19.670 --> 17:21.040
I can't help you.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.960
Okay.

17:25.040 --> 17:28.120
My vagina hurts.
Like, a lot.

17:28.120 --> 17:29.830
-Ah. Okay.
-Yeah.

17:29.830 --> 17:32.500
Um, well,
I should have a --

17:32.500 --> 17:33.920
May I have a look?

17:33.920 --> 17:36.290
You've already been
all up in there, so...

17:36.290 --> 17:38.170
In for a penny,
I suppose.
All right.

17:38.170 --> 17:42.120
So, I'm just gonna have you put
your knees straight up for me

17:42.120 --> 17:44.120
with your ankles together,
and then drop your knees.

17:44.120 --> 17:46.000
Yeah, just like that.

17:46.000 --> 17:47.750
Okay, give me
just a second.

17:47.750 --> 17:49.210
Okay.

17:49.210 --> 17:50.170
Okay.

17:51.750 --> 17:53.420
Okay.
I see the problem here.

17:53.420 --> 17:56.080
You have a pretty significant
vulvar hematoma.

17:56.080 --> 17:57.620
"Vulvar"?
No, thank you.

17:57.620 --> 18:00.290
It's a blood clot. The swelling
is causing your pain.

18:00.290 --> 18:03.210
I can drain it for you,
and you'll feel 100% better.

18:03.210 --> 18:06.420
Okay. A blood clot?

18:06.420 --> 18:08.920
Yes, caused by bleeding
directed toward the skin

18:08.920 --> 18:11.210
where the loose tissue doesn't
have much resistance to --

18:11.210 --> 18:14.040
I'm sorry. Can you talk about
something else? Anything else.

18:14.040 --> 18:16.250
-[ Chuckles ]
-Yeah. Um...

18:16.250 --> 18:17.710
[ Drawer slides ]

18:17.710 --> 18:20.460
So how did, uh -- How did you
and -- and Matthew meet?

18:20.460 --> 18:23.080
Oh, let's, uh, let's go back
to my loose tissue.

18:24.500 --> 18:27.380
I'm sorry. This is --
This is weird.

18:27.380 --> 18:30.080
It is.

18:30.080 --> 18:33.500
But God doesn't give us more
than we can handle, right?

18:35.170 --> 18:37.080
I was just saying that
to someone.

18:37.080 --> 18:39.000
[ Both chuckle ]

18:40.790 --> 18:43.000
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:43.000 --> 18:44.670
[ Radio chatter,
monitor beeping ]

18:47.750 --> 18:49.420
Look at him.

18:49.420 --> 18:52.960
Protecting us from a 12-year-old
strapped into a CT.

18:52.960 --> 18:55.670
That is our tax dollars
hard at work.

18:55.670 --> 18:58.210
-He's just doing his job.
-That's what they always say.

18:58.210 --> 18:59.880
What about the cop
that shot the boy?

18:59.880 --> 19:01.420
He also just
doing his job?

19:01.420 --> 19:03.290
I have seen soldiers get
so wound up with stress,

19:03.290 --> 19:05.540
they just shoot first
before they even know
what they're shooting at.

19:05.540 --> 19:07.250
And you think
that's okay?

19:07.250 --> 19:10.290
No, I don't. No.
No, that's a war zone.

19:10.290 --> 19:12.460
This was an upper-class
neighborhood.

19:12.460 --> 19:14.710
Yeah, those can be the
worst neighborhoods for us.

19:14.710 --> 19:16.250
I grew up in those
neighborhoods.

19:16.250 --> 19:18.460
Just being there
is suspicious.

19:18.460 --> 19:20.710
Constantly stopped for
"fitting the description."

19:20.710 --> 19:22.710
I remember I was walking,
carrying these speakers

19:22.710 --> 19:24.540
for my friend, and these cops
pulled up on me.

19:24.540 --> 19:25.920
Car screeches to a halt.

19:25.920 --> 19:27.170
They jump out, guns drawn,

19:27.170 --> 19:28.710
yelling at me
to drop everything,

19:28.710 --> 19:30.710
slam me into the car,
handcuff me.

19:30.710 --> 19:33.210
I mean, I was one block
from my front door.

19:36.540 --> 19:38.000
You n--
You never told me that.

19:38.000 --> 19:39.750
Well, doesn't really come up
until it does.

19:39.750 --> 19:41.750
[ Beeping ]
The scans are up.

19:41.750 --> 19:43.040
Jackson:
Yeah, there it is.

19:43.040 --> 19:45.620
Can track the bullet
right by the carotid.

19:45.620 --> 19:49.580
But the vessel wall is intact,
though, so he's gonna be okay.

19:49.580 --> 19:54.380
Uh, we'll keep him for
observation. IV antibiotics.

19:54.380 --> 19:56.380
But this could've been
so much worse.

19:58.830 --> 20:01.080
They took
his childhood today.

20:02.330 --> 20:05.080
He's never
gonna be the same.

20:06.210 --> 20:09.500
[ Ringtone chimes ]

20:09.500 --> 20:11.710
[ Sighs ]

20:11.710 --> 20:13.620
I have to get back.

20:19.120 --> 20:21.580
Taryn: I'm so sorry, Mr. Taylor.
It's out of my control.

20:21.580 --> 20:23.620
I'm sorry. If you could
just check and see if
there's a room available.

20:23.620 --> 20:26.290
Why hasn't Mrs. Taylor been
sent up to a room yet?!
I, uh --

20:26.290 --> 20:29.830
Call L&D, call postpartum, call
somebody and make it happen!

20:29.830 --> 20:31.290
Taryn: Yes, ma'am.

20:34.670 --> 20:36.920
How have you been?

20:36.920 --> 20:40.080
Good. Really good.
And you?

20:40.080 --> 20:42.460
I mean, how's Ruby?

20:42.460 --> 20:45.120
"Ruby." So pretty.
Um, how -- how is she?

20:45.120 --> 20:48.250
She's good.

20:48.250 --> 20:50.330
Thank you.
Dr. Robbins says she's good.

20:53.790 --> 20:55.580
Karin is terrific.

20:55.580 --> 20:58.460
Yeah, she is.

20:58.460 --> 21:00.170
It's the best thing
that ever happened to me.

21:01.500 --> 21:04.120
And I guess I have you
to thank for that.

21:05.790 --> 21:08.710
I mean, it hurt, being left
on my wedding day.

21:08.710 --> 21:10.500
Matthew, I'm so sorry --

21:10.500 --> 21:12.790
At my wedding in front of
everyone I knew and loved.

21:12.790 --> 21:14.120
It hurt.

21:17.540 --> 21:19.620
And I wasn't open to
being hurt again like that,

21:19.620 --> 21:22.580
so Karin and I...

21:22.580 --> 21:25.420
we had a long friendship

21:25.420 --> 21:28.500
before I let myself realize
that she was...

21:30.170 --> 21:31.420
She's the love of my life,
you know?

21:33.330 --> 21:35.080
Of course you know.

21:35.080 --> 21:36.710
You [Scoffs] --
You have that with Jackson.

21:39.460 --> 21:42.460
And I h-heard from the pastor
that you were pregnant,

21:42.460 --> 21:45.080
so you have, what,
a 3-year-old now?

21:47.710 --> 21:49.580
I had a -- I have...

21:49.580 --> 21:52.000
[ Chuckles ]
We have Harriet.

21:52.000 --> 21:53.960
We have a beautiful daughter
named Harriet.

21:53.960 --> 21:57.420
She's 1. And she's
the light of my life.

21:59.920 --> 22:02.040
Well...

22:02.040 --> 22:04.460
Guess it worked out perfectly
for both of us, then.

22:04.460 --> 22:06.750
God used that pain

22:06.750 --> 22:09.710
and turned it into
something beautiful.

22:09.710 --> 22:12.290
Guess He knew what He was
doing all along, huh?

22:16.880 --> 22:19.250
I am so glad
you found Karin.

22:19.250 --> 22:21.670
Yeah. Uh...
[ Clears throat ]

22:21.670 --> 22:22.830
I should get back.

22:35.330 --> 22:38.830
My injuries are stable.
I'm fine to go.

22:38.830 --> 22:40.460
Dr. Stadler, you should
stay for observation

22:40.460 --> 22:41.710
for at least 24 hours.

22:41.710 --> 22:43.750
You know, let him go.
He's a doctor.

22:43.750 --> 22:45.120
If he wants
to walk around

22:45.120 --> 22:47.460
with fractured ribs and
a concussion, let him.

22:47.460 --> 22:50.000
He's alert and oriented.

22:50.000 --> 22:52.290
Are you the fiancée?

22:52.290 --> 22:54.580
Maybe you can talk
some sense into him.

22:54.580 --> 22:57.040
This is not a good idea.
Wha--

22:57.040 --> 22:58.620
Why are you with Brooke?

22:58.620 --> 23:00.000
'Cause she doesn't want
to be alone with you.

23:00.000 --> 23:02.460
[ Chuckles ]

23:02.460 --> 23:05.210
Oh, why am I not surprised
that you tried to poison her

23:05.210 --> 23:07.330
while I wasn't even able
to defend myself?

23:07.330 --> 23:10.830
Jenny, get my stuff.
I'm not staying here.

23:10.830 --> 23:12.040
No.

23:17.620 --> 23:19.500
Babe.

23:19.500 --> 23:23.210
I'm really trying here,
but you got to meet me halfway.

23:23.210 --> 23:27.210
[ Scoffs ]
I know I'm not perfect.

23:27.210 --> 23:30.040
You are way closer to that
than I am.

23:30.040 --> 23:33.580
But, please, can we just leave
this place and not look back?

23:33.580 --> 23:35.170
We have
a wedding to plan.

23:35.170 --> 23:37.960
[ Exhales sharply ]

23:37.960 --> 23:39.710
You should probably
call your office

23:39.710 --> 23:41.670
and let them know you're gonna
be gone for a few days.

23:41.670 --> 23:43.120
That's my girl.

23:43.120 --> 23:45.830
Or, like, 10 to 20 years.

23:45.830 --> 23:47.380
What?

23:47.380 --> 23:49.210
I'm gonna talk
to the police, Paul.

23:49.210 --> 23:50.790
I'm gonna tell them every time
you ever hurt me.

23:50.790 --> 23:52.120
Every kick, every slap.
[ Sighs ]

23:52.120 --> 23:53.750
You put your hands around
my throat last night,

23:53.750 --> 23:56.330
so that's not just
domestic violence.
That's attempted murder.

23:56.330 --> 23:59.040
-Will you testify?
-Yes.

23:59.040 --> 24:01.080
You sound crazy.

24:01.080 --> 24:02.290
No, she doesn't.
No, I don't.
Not at all.

24:02.290 --> 24:04.670
Jenny, I'm the
well-known physician,

24:04.670 --> 24:08.040
and you're...nobody.

24:08.040 --> 24:10.500
All you're gonna do is throw
your career in the garbage.

24:10.500 --> 24:12.620
No one's gonna hire
someone they don't trust.

24:12.620 --> 24:15.080
No, I'm not gonna let you scare
me into backing down again.

24:15.080 --> 24:16.830
Scare you? I'm the one
who should be scared.

24:16.830 --> 24:18.420
You're threatening me
in a hospital bed.

24:18.420 --> 24:20.120
I-I'm defenseless.

24:21.250 --> 24:24.460
Please.
Can we just talk?

24:24.460 --> 24:27.920
Some very broken part of me
still loves you, Paul,

24:27.920 --> 24:29.710
but let me be very clear --

24:29.710 --> 24:31.750
I am never
speaking to you again

24:31.750 --> 24:33.460
unless it's from
a witness stand.

24:33.460 --> 24:35.960
You stupid bitch.

24:35.960 --> 24:37.830
You're not going
to the police!

24:37.830 --> 24:39.250
You're not
walking out on me!

24:39.250 --> 24:40.750
[ Gasping ]

24:40.750 --> 24:50.040
♪♪

24:50.040 --> 24:51.960
His pulse is thready,
and he's not breathing.

24:51.960 --> 24:53.420
We should get
a crash cart in here.

25:05.880 --> 25:07.210
Uh, it's a simple repair.

25:07.210 --> 25:09.170
We just re-anastomose
the flexor tendons,

25:09.170 --> 25:11.500
and he should have a shot
at regaining motion.

25:11.500 --> 25:15.960
Cool. And why'd you page
Dr. DeLuca? Isn't she an OB?

25:15.960 --> 25:17.580
The psych consult
was taking a while,

25:17.580 --> 25:21.000
so I thought I'd bring in
a...expert in the field.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.500
[ Clears throat ]

25:22.500 --> 25:24.250
Carina:
And it's good for you.

25:24.250 --> 25:26.210
Studies show
it can increase productivity,

25:26.210 --> 25:29.250
gain confidence,
improve your self-esteem.

25:29.250 --> 25:30.960
There is even
some evidence to say

25:30.960 --> 25:33.250
that it helps lower the
likelihood of prostate cancer.

25:33.250 --> 25:35.040
Vik: Really?

25:35.040 --> 25:37.750
God not only make our
reproductive organs,

25:37.750 --> 25:39.420
He made pleasure centers.

25:39.420 --> 25:40.750
And He did not only

25:40.750 --> 25:42.670
make them pleasurable enough
for procreation,

25:42.670 --> 25:44.790
He made them
immensely pleasurable.

25:44.790 --> 25:47.830
And I do not believe He gave us
all these things by mistake.

25:47.830 --> 25:51.380
Life is so painful sometimes
and so stressful,

25:51.380 --> 25:55.120
and He gifted us with
a built-in pressure release.

25:55.120 --> 25:57.380
Vik: Copy...that.

26:00.080 --> 26:02.920
David, I-I'm saying
everybody does it.

26:02.920 --> 26:05.880
Men, women, animal kingdom.

26:05.880 --> 26:07.170
Everybody in this room.

26:07.170 --> 26:09.420
Let's n-not.

26:11.170 --> 26:13.080
Well, I do it,
and I'm not ashamed.

26:14.920 --> 26:17.170
Uh...uh,
you have to leave.

26:17.170 --> 26:19.330
You have to leave
right now.

26:20.710 --> 26:22.580
Y-Yeah, okay.

26:22.580 --> 26:30.920
♪♪

26:30.920 --> 26:34.170
What does "second-impact
syndrome" mean?

26:34.170 --> 26:35.710
It means he got
a second concussion

26:35.710 --> 26:37.460
before the first one healed,
and his brain herniated.

26:39.880 --> 26:41.540
Is he brain-dead?

26:41.540 --> 26:43.670
We can't say with certainty
for a few more hours,

26:43.670 --> 26:45.170
but it appears that way.

26:45.170 --> 26:47.710
I'm -- I'm very --
I'm sorry.

26:47.710 --> 26:50.290
Are you comfortable talking
to her about her options?

26:50.290 --> 26:51.330
Yes.

26:55.040 --> 26:56.540
What does she mean
by "options"?

26:56.540 --> 26:58.250
Alex: Well, she means
you have to decide

26:58.250 --> 26:59.710
if you want to withdraw
his life support.

26:59.710 --> 27:01.670
Meredith: Alex.

27:01.670 --> 27:02.920
It's not up to her.

27:05.120 --> 27:08.120
Oh, my God. It's me.

27:09.170 --> 27:11.120
I'm still legally
his wife.

27:13.620 --> 27:15.080
[ Laughing ]
Oh, my God.

27:15.080 --> 27:23.000
[ Jo laughing hysterically ]

27:23.000 --> 27:24.710
Oh, my God.

27:24.710 --> 27:26.460
I'm so sorry.

27:26.460 --> 27:30.460
[ Laughing hysterically ]

27:30.460 --> 27:34.580
I'm so sorry. Crap.
I'm so sorry.

27:34.580 --> 27:36.080
I'm so sorry.

27:39.580 --> 27:41.920
[ Sobbing ]

27:48.250 --> 27:50.880
I called Dr. Robbins,
but her pulse is racing,
and she rates her pain as a 10.

27:50.880 --> 27:52.290
Okay, let's send
for a urinalysis

27:52.290 --> 27:54.830
and make sure to get LFTs
and a coag panel.

27:54.830 --> 27:56.670
Okay, your BP's
slightly elevated.

27:56.670 --> 27:58.000
Do you have a history
of high blood pressure?

27:58.000 --> 27:59.120
-It's usually low. Ow!
-No.

27:59.120 --> 28:00.710
Hey, Karin.
What's the problem?

28:00.710 --> 28:02.580
-Where have you been?
-I had an emergency surgery.

28:02.580 --> 28:04.500
On Ruby?
No, no, no. Ruby's fine.
What's going on?

28:04.500 --> 28:05.880
Okay, her BP's
a little elevated,

28:05.880 --> 28:07.330
and her abdomen
is extremely tender.

28:07.330 --> 28:09.250
[ Monitor beeping rapidly
in distance ]
Okay. All right.

28:09.250 --> 28:11.960
Go, go, go. I've got her.
Let me see this hand.

28:11.960 --> 28:13.750
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

28:13.750 --> 28:15.040
What happened?!

28:15.040 --> 28:16.580
-One of epi!
-Carotid blew.

28:16.580 --> 28:18.500
Hematoma closed his airway,
and we lost his vitals.

28:18.500 --> 28:20.040
The shock wave
from the bullet

28:20.040 --> 28:22.290
must've weakened the carotid
wall, and it ruptured.

28:22.290 --> 28:23.580
Okay.
Let's get him to the OR.

28:23.580 --> 28:25.210
I'll take over compressions
on the way.

28:25.210 --> 28:27.170
All right. You heard her.
Take that.

28:27.170 --> 28:28.540
We all set?

28:28.540 --> 28:30.620
Move, move, move.
Ready.

28:30.620 --> 28:33.460
♪ Understands the demons ♪
Boy: Mommy, what --
what's happening?

28:33.460 --> 28:35.250
What's happening to Eric?

28:35.250 --> 28:38.670
[ Sobbing ] He's my baby.
He's my baby.

28:38.670 --> 28:40.000
It's gonna be okay.

28:40.000 --> 28:42.000
♪ When they are winning ♪

28:42.000 --> 28:43.750
-He's my baby.
-He's gonna be okay.

28:43.750 --> 28:46.000
♪ And I go spinning
all night ♪
He's gonna be okay.

28:46.000 --> 28:48.670
♪ Screaming,
"I don't need your help ♪

28:48.670 --> 28:53.080
♪ He knows that means
I need it bad ♪

28:53.080 --> 28:55.080
Bailey: Okay.
Whole compressions.

28:55.080 --> 28:57.500
We got a pulse!

28:57.500 --> 29:02.420
♪ My father
understands the demons ♪

29:02.420 --> 29:04.580
On my count.
One, two, and three.

29:04.580 --> 29:06.420
Hang another unit
of blood.

29:06.420 --> 29:08.420
Jackson: Let get set up for
a post-op angio, please.

29:08.420 --> 29:10.500
♪ And knows what to say
when they are winning ♪

29:10.500 --> 29:12.750
-Chief, where do you want me?
-Uh, we got it, Kepner.

29:12.750 --> 29:14.880
-Thank you.
-Jackson, do you need any help?

29:14.880 --> 29:16.960
All right, I want to
get him prepped all the
way down to his knees.

29:16.960 --> 29:18.460
♪ ...need your help ♪

29:18.460 --> 29:22.750
♪ He knows that means
I need it bad ♪

29:22.750 --> 29:25.040
[ Monitor beeping ]

29:25.040 --> 29:28.710
Jackson: Okay. Thank you.

29:28.710 --> 29:30.670
[ Radio chatter ]

29:30.670 --> 29:32.670
How's it going?
Is he okay?

29:32.670 --> 29:35.830
♪ My father
understands the demons ♪

29:35.830 --> 29:38.210
♪ I wrestle with
in my daydream ♪

29:38.210 --> 29:40.250
We're gonna need
to get a statement.

29:40.250 --> 29:44.290
♪ He knows that means
I need it bad ♪

29:44.290 --> 29:46.080
April: Oh, my God.
What happened?

29:46.080 --> 29:47.920
Arizona: She's bleeding out.
Why didn't you call me sooner?!

29:47.920 --> 29:49.670
I called you as soon
as she was in distress.

29:49.670 --> 29:51.080
She was sitting
in your ER for hours!

29:51.080 --> 29:52.620
How many times
did you check her?

29:52.620 --> 29:54.750
Every 20 minutes.
One BP was mildly elevated.

29:54.750 --> 29:57.420
-What is it?
-It's DIC and HELLP syndrome.

29:57.420 --> 29:59.460
Her liver's failing,
and the other organs
are trying to follow.

29:59.460 --> 30:01.040
Okay. What can I do to help?
I can scrub in --

30:01.040 --> 30:02.380
God! I can't stop
this bleeding!

30:02.380 --> 30:03.500
All right. We're gonna
have to do a hysterectomy.

30:03.500 --> 30:04.880
DeLuca, go talk to
Karin's husband.

30:04.880 --> 30:06.580
No, no, no. You take care
of her. I'll go. I'll talk to --

30:06.580 --> 30:08.830
Arizona: No, April!
Please leave him alone.

30:08.830 --> 30:11.120
-Clamp.
-Okay. Dr. Robbins --

30:11.120 --> 30:13.330
I got it, I got it.
Go, go, go.

30:13.330 --> 30:15.170
♪ ...need your help ♪

30:15.170 --> 30:17.210
Oh, my God.
♪ He knows that means
I need it bad ♪

30:27.040 --> 30:29.500
I came to pray,
but I can go.

30:29.500 --> 30:37.580
♪♪

30:37.580 --> 30:45.460
♪♪

30:45.460 --> 30:53.290
♪♪

30:53.290 --> 31:01.250
♪♪

31:01.250 --> 31:03.460
[ Breathing sharply ]

31:03.460 --> 31:09.920
♪♪

31:09.920 --> 31:16.420
♪♪

31:16.420 --> 31:23.120
♪♪

31:23.120 --> 31:25.710
[ Monitor beeping ]

31:25.710 --> 31:28.080
-It was a drunk driver.
-What?!

31:28.080 --> 31:31.540
They found the guy who hit Paul.
It was a drunk driver.

31:31.540 --> 31:33.880
So nobody
has to go to Canada.

31:33.880 --> 31:35.750
-[ Chuckles ]
-She's free.

31:38.330 --> 31:41.380
What happens if we
leave him plugged in?

31:41.380 --> 31:45.000
His organs will shut down.
He won't last for long.

31:47.210 --> 31:49.920
I wanted him
to rot in jail.

31:49.920 --> 31:53.170
I wanted to stand up and tell
the whole world what he did.

31:53.170 --> 31:54.960
I wanted to
stand up in court

31:54.960 --> 31:57.460
and humiliate him
the way he humiliated me.

31:59.620 --> 32:02.330
When I was with him,
he didn't smoke or drink.

32:02.330 --> 32:05.540
Is that still true?

32:05.540 --> 32:09.540
Yeah. He jogs five miles a day.
No red meat. Why?

32:09.540 --> 32:12.080
Because I know
what to do.

32:15.750 --> 32:17.540
[ Telephone rings ]

32:17.540 --> 32:21.790
Did you know that Seattle is
a city built on top of a city?

32:21.790 --> 32:23.620
[ Mouse clicks ]
Um, have you been to --

32:23.620 --> 32:26.420
Ah, what's its name?
The -- The -- The Underground?

32:26.420 --> 32:28.880
Her baseline pressure
was low.
Sorry?

32:28.880 --> 32:30.210
My patient,
Karin Taylor.

32:30.210 --> 32:32.420
A high BP for her is a normal BP
for anyone else,

32:32.420 --> 32:34.620
so when she was showing signs
of preeclampsia, she --

32:34.620 --> 32:38.120
Her blood pressure seemed to
be normal, so no one saw it.

32:38.120 --> 32:39.460
Yeah.
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

32:39.460 --> 32:41.170
Dr. Robbins, she's in PEA.
I just lost her pulse.

32:41.170 --> 32:43.330
Arizona: Matthew, I need you
to get out of here, honey.

32:43.330 --> 32:44.880
Matthew: Don't take her away.
I'm begging you.

32:44.880 --> 32:46.750
Okay, stop.

32:46.750 --> 32:48.540
Matthew: Please. Just put your
wisdom in these doctors' hands.

32:48.540 --> 32:50.620
Okay. Hey, somebody's got to
get him out of here, please!

32:50.620 --> 32:53.210
-Don't take her away from me.
-Matthew, you got to go!

32:53.210 --> 32:55.790
We're maxed out on pressors
and had to stop dialysis
before she started coding.

32:55.790 --> 32:57.620
Okay.
Let's get ECMO set up.

32:57.620 --> 32:59.710
As soon as we get her back,
I want it ready. One of epi.

32:59.710 --> 33:03.250
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

33:03.250 --> 33:05.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:05.250 --> 33:07.580
[ Radio chatter ]

33:10.250 --> 33:13.540
[ Indistinct conversation ]

33:13.540 --> 33:15.380
[ Sobbing ]

33:17.830 --> 33:20.000
[ Sobbing continues ]

33:20.000 --> 33:23.330
Danisha:
Oh, my God! No!

33:23.330 --> 33:26.710
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, my God! No!

33:26.710 --> 33:29.380
No!

33:29.380 --> 33:31.000
[ Door opens ]

33:31.000 --> 33:32.830
[ Danisha sobbing ]

33:34.210 --> 33:36.380
Jackson. Jackson.

33:36.380 --> 33:38.330
It was a high-pressure
situation.

33:38.330 --> 33:40.250
An officer made
a judgment call.
No.

33:40.250 --> 33:42.920
There's no judgment in that
call. That was just a reaction.

33:42.920 --> 33:44.750
You see skin color.
We all do.

33:44.750 --> 33:47.000
But the reaction that
you give to a white kid

33:47.000 --> 33:49.330
versus a brown kid
in that split second?

33:49.330 --> 33:50.960
That's the measurable,
fixable difference.

33:50.960 --> 33:52.540
Bias is human.

33:52.540 --> 33:55.250
You have guns.

33:55.250 --> 33:58.750
You're using guns.
So yours is lethal.

33:58.750 --> 34:00.580
We aren't racist.

34:00.580 --> 34:02.500
We just never know
who has a gun.

34:02.500 --> 34:04.960
I didn't say anything about
racist. I said biased.

34:04.960 --> 34:07.500
And lucky for us,
bias is fixable.

34:07.500 --> 34:09.290
You have protocols
in place.

34:09.290 --> 34:12.750
Those can be adjusted.
You can fix it.

34:12.750 --> 34:14.920
Or you can keep pretending
that it doesn't exist at all.

34:14.920 --> 34:16.670
Kids are dying.

34:16.670 --> 34:20.330
This kid is dead.
For what?

34:20.330 --> 34:25.080
So many people that look
just like him are dying.

34:25.080 --> 34:27.040
For what?

34:32.460 --> 34:34.920
Doctor. I'm sorry, but
we still need a statement.

34:36.880 --> 34:39.250
My statement is that
a little boy was at home

34:39.250 --> 34:42.330
when your fellow officer
shot and killed him.

34:42.330 --> 34:45.120
You can't just be out there
shooting people

34:45.120 --> 34:46.790
'cause you're afraid.

34:46.790 --> 34:50.210
How am I supposed to have any
faith in a system like that?

35:00.920 --> 35:03.540
[ Ship horn blares ]

35:03.540 --> 35:07.830
Bailey: 12 years old.
In his own house.

35:07.830 --> 35:09.790
It's time to give Tuck
the talk.

35:09.790 --> 35:11.080
Ben: I know.

35:18.000 --> 35:19.830
[ Telephone rings ]

35:19.830 --> 35:21.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

35:23.920 --> 35:26.460
-[ Sighs ] You paged?
-Uh, yes.

35:26.460 --> 35:28.170
Well, I just telling David

35:28.170 --> 35:30.710
with a little rehab he should
make a complete recovery.

35:30.710 --> 35:32.250
Okay.

35:32.250 --> 35:34.790
And he, uh, had a few questions
I couldn't answer.

35:36.040 --> 35:38.170
You know scripture, right?

35:38.170 --> 35:41.040
We'll leave you to it.

35:41.040 --> 35:43.000
Yeah.

35:43.000 --> 35:44.790
A or B --

35:44.790 --> 35:48.080
God created the Earth in seven
days, or evolution happened?

35:48.080 --> 35:50.120
Both. 2 Peter says
that with the Lord,

35:50.120 --> 35:53.290
a day is like a thousand years,
so He measures time differently,

35:53.290 --> 35:56.040
which means he could have used
evolution to create the world.

35:56.040 --> 35:59.420
Do you think that Jonah
really survived three days
in the belly of a great fish?

35:59.420 --> 36:02.000
[ Sighs ] The Bible is --
is a book, David.

36:02.000 --> 36:05.000
It's full of beautiful stories
and metaphors and -- and poems

36:05.000 --> 36:06.620
that shouldn't be taken
literally.

36:06.620 --> 36:09.420
But 2 Timothy says all scripture
is inspired by God.

36:09.420 --> 36:11.170
Yeah, inspired by,
not dictated by.

36:11.170 --> 36:12.540
What about
"thou shalt not kill"?

36:12.540 --> 36:14.960
Well, come on. That one
is definitely literal.

36:14.960 --> 36:17.750
Aren't they all?
Luke says "Blessed are those

36:17.750 --> 36:20.120
who hear the word of God
and obey it."

36:20.120 --> 36:21.670
-I know. I know He --
-James says, "Do not merely

36:21.670 --> 36:23.120
listen to the word.

36:23.120 --> 36:25.710
Do what it says."
Within reason!

36:25.710 --> 36:28.040
You have to do what it says
within reason, okay?!

36:28.040 --> 36:31.210
We don't chop off our limps! We
don't cut our babies in half!

36:31.210 --> 36:32.960
Then tell me what to do
if this won't!

36:32.960 --> 36:35.290
If I can't trust this,
if it's not the truth,

36:35.290 --> 36:37.330
if the Word of God is just
a bunch of stories,

36:37.330 --> 36:39.380
what does anything mean?

36:39.380 --> 36:41.040
What is any of this
even for?

36:45.750 --> 36:48.670
I am William George
Bailey Jones.

36:48.670 --> 36:50.330
I'm 13 years old.

36:50.330 --> 36:52.380
And I have nothing
to harm you.

36:52.380 --> 36:53.880
Bailey:
That's good, baby.

36:53.880 --> 36:56.880
You always have to show the
police where your hands are.

36:56.880 --> 36:59.750
And always say what you're doing
before you do it.

36:59.750 --> 37:02.250
Ben: Be in control
of your emotions.

37:02.250 --> 37:04.170
Be polite and --
and respectful.

37:04.170 --> 37:06.540
Yeah, don't fight back.
Don't talk back.

37:06.540 --> 37:08.460
Do not make
any sudden movements.

37:08.460 --> 37:11.330
Remember, your only goal
is to get home safely.

37:11.330 --> 37:14.920
If you get detained,
don't sign anything

37:14.920 --> 37:16.380
or -- or write anything.

37:16.380 --> 37:18.540
Wait for a parent
before you talk.

37:18.540 --> 37:20.170
And if your white friends

37:20.170 --> 37:22.170
are saying things
or mouthing off,

37:22.170 --> 37:24.290
know that you cannot.

37:24.290 --> 37:27.290
You can't go climbing
through windows,

37:27.290 --> 37:30.210
play with toy guns,
throw rocks.

37:30.210 --> 37:33.000
And you cannot ever
run away from them,

37:33.000 --> 37:35.000
no matter how afraid you are.

37:35.000 --> 37:37.710
Never, never...

37:37.710 --> 37:39.670
never run.

37:39.670 --> 37:42.040
[ Thunder rumbles ]

37:44.500 --> 37:47.120
Everything that
we're saying to you

37:47.120 --> 37:50.040
we're saying because we want you
to come home again.

37:50.040 --> 37:52.500
We want you to grow up

37:52.500 --> 37:56.040
to be anything and everything
that you want to be.

37:56.040 --> 37:59.040
Do you hear me?

37:59.040 --> 38:02.880
You...are amazing.

38:02.880 --> 38:04.920
You are perfect.

38:07.580 --> 38:10.170
And we want you
to stay that way.

38:10.170 --> 38:15.830
♪♪

38:15.830 --> 38:18.210
♪ Wake up ♪

38:18.210 --> 38:21.000
Am I even allowed
to be in here?

38:21.000 --> 38:22.540
You're fine.

38:22.540 --> 38:23.920
♪ Stay with me ♪

38:26.920 --> 38:30.830
♪ This is all ♪

38:30.830 --> 38:34.420
♪ Just a bad dream ♪

38:34.420 --> 38:36.170
Jo: This is a good one.

38:36.170 --> 38:40.670
His kidney's going to
a little girl in Billings.

38:40.670 --> 38:44.040
Do you think he's evil?

38:44.040 --> 38:47.500
I mean, I'm a scientist,

38:47.500 --> 38:49.210
and I think
I'm an atheist.

38:49.210 --> 38:51.500
But there's a little part of me
that's worried

38:51.500 --> 38:54.380
that the girl in Billings
is getting an evil kidney.

38:54.380 --> 38:56.960
Hmm.

38:56.960 --> 38:59.920
I don't believe that
anyone is just evil.

38:59.920 --> 39:03.750
If people were just one thing,
life would be so much simpler.

39:03.750 --> 39:06.920
Paul was awful in this life,

39:06.920 --> 39:11.080
but now, in death,
he gets to do all this good.

39:11.080 --> 39:14.750
So there's light
and darkness,

39:14.750 --> 39:16.750
and they both coexist.

39:16.750 --> 39:21.170
And sometimes
it's really beautiful.

39:21.170 --> 39:24.380
♪ Half in the light,
I need to know now ♪

39:24.380 --> 39:27.040
♪ Are you with me? ♪

39:27.040 --> 39:31.000
♪ Are you in or are you out? ♪

39:31.000 --> 39:33.420
Helm, I never followed up
on Paul Stadler.

39:33.420 --> 39:35.580
-Just a concussion, right?
-No.

39:35.580 --> 39:38.460
I, uh -- Yes.
It was a concussion.

39:38.460 --> 39:40.920
But, Dr. Kepner, he died.

39:40.920 --> 39:44.460
What? No.
He was fine! What?!

39:44.460 --> 39:46.170
I'm sorry. I don't --
I don't know.

39:46.170 --> 39:47.750
Um, I'll find out.

39:47.750 --> 39:53.250
♪♪

39:53.250 --> 39:54.620
Hey.

39:54.620 --> 39:59.920
♪♪

39:59.920 --> 40:04.960
♪♪

40:07.080 --> 40:09.880
♪ Are you with me? ♪

40:09.880 --> 40:11.460
♪ Are you in... ♪

40:11.460 --> 40:13.920
April: "Eli, Eli...

40:13.920 --> 40:17.750
lama sabachthani?"

40:17.750 --> 40:19.880
That's what Jesus said
on the cross before he died.

40:19.880 --> 40:22.460
♪ Are you with me? ♪

40:22.460 --> 40:26.960
"My God, My God.
Why have you forsaken me?"

40:26.960 --> 40:29.290
♪♪

40:29.290 --> 40:31.830
Job asked the question, too.

40:31.830 --> 40:33.620
But he kept the faith.

40:33.620 --> 40:36.250
♪ Equal parts light and dark ♪

40:36.250 --> 40:38.040
And what did he get for it?

40:38.040 --> 40:39.880
♪ We can be brilliant ♪

40:39.880 --> 40:42.000
Replacement children. PTSD.

40:42.000 --> 40:44.330
♪ Are you with me? ♪

40:44.330 --> 40:48.210
Was it worth it to have been
a faithful servant?

40:48.210 --> 40:49.540
Or would it have been better

40:49.540 --> 40:52.540
to just curse God's name
from the beginning?

40:52.540 --> 40:55.460
♪ Oh, are you... ♪

40:55.460 --> 40:59.960
Where was God throughout all
of Job's suffering and pain?

40:59.960 --> 41:02.960
♪ Are you in or are you out? ♪

41:02.960 --> 41:04.790
He was winning
a bet with Satan.

41:04.790 --> 41:07.290
Vik: Rough day, huh?

41:07.290 --> 41:09.080
♪ Are you in or are you out? ♪

41:12.670 --> 41:15.540
♪ Are you with me? ♪

41:15.540 --> 41:21.170
♪♪

